{
  "texts": [
    "Exact copy of instruction was more common in the first session (65) and decreased in subsequent sessions (to 32 and 27, respectively).",
    "This decline might be due to the demo training where students were advised to ask their questions in parts to get more accurate answers from ChatGPT.",
    "However, when considering the total written prompts across the three sessions, exact copy of instruction, partial copy of instruction, and summary of instruction collectively constituted the highest number, totaling 465 prompts (19.47% of the total prompts).",
    "This suggests a reliance on ChatGPT while solving programming tasks and the ease of copy-pasting task instructions.",
    "On the other hand, coding task inquiry (264 prompts; 11.06% of total prompts) and refining GPT code (244 prompts; 10.22% of total prompts) were consistently high relative to other prompt types."
  ]
}